"'''A Boy and His Monster: The Rancor Keeper's Tale'''" is a short story by [[Kevin J. Anderson]] that provides the backstory for [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|Jabba's rancor]] and [[Malakili/Legends|Malakili]], the [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] keeper. It was published in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', which was published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]].

==Plot summary==
When the fearsome [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] monster is found in a shipwreck in [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine's]] [[Dune Sea/Legends|Dune Sea]], [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] underlings present it as a gift to the [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]]. Jabba tasks [[Malakili/Legends|Malakili]] with the care and feeding of his new pet. Malakili is overjoyed to have custody of [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|Jabba's rancor]], but he resents the captivity of what he considers so magnificent a beast. Over time, he and the rancor develop a certain rapport, which convinces Malakili that he must find a way to free the rancor. To this end he makes an agreement with Jabba's local rival, Lady [[Valarian/Legends|Valarian]], to transport both himself and the rancor to a remote [[Planet/Legends|planet]] where they might live together untroubled by others. However, the date set for the escape fatefully coincides with the arrival of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], who [[Death/Legends|kills]] the creature, thereby upsetting Malakili's plans.

==Continuity==
The [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|rancor's]] arrival on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] was first described in ''[[The Star Wars Sourcebook]]'' ([[1987]]), a roleplaying gamebook published by [[West End Games]]. The date of the rancor's arrival is kept vague in that source, but has subsequently being pegged at about [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]] since [[Bidlo Kwerve/Legends|Bidlo Kwerve]], the rancor's first victim, is seen alive and well in ''[[Rebel Dawn]]'' ([[1997]]).<ref name="TERC" />

